  "text": "There has been much speculation on interrelationships between diet, intestinal bacteria, and colon cancer (for a review, see reference 13) . Studies in this area have been hampered by the lack of a rapid, simple assay for identifying and enumerating the species of intestinal bacteria and for analyzing large numbers of specimens. Conventional procedures for identifying bacterial species, especially in the case of anaerobes, are cumbersome and time consuming [CITATION_1] .",
